channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Israel-Gaza-Lebanon updates: IDF claims Hezbollah was planning 'invasion' of Israel
item.description: Israeli troops are now active in southern Lebanon in what the Israel Defense Forces called "limited, localized, and targeted ground raids" targeting Hezbollah positions.

item.title: Satellite Footage Shows Typhoon Intensifying as It Nears Taiwan
Man gets prison for cloning giant sheep for captive trophy hunting
item.description: Arthur "Jack" Schubarth allegedly used tissue and testicles from large sheep hunted in Central Asia and the U.S. to create hybrid sheep for captive trophy hunting.

item.title: Russian jet comes within 50 feet of US fighter off coast of Alaska
item.description: A Russian fighter jet came within 50 feet of an American fighter during a NORAD intercept off of Alaska.

item.title: Many Dockworkers Make $150,000 or More. Why They’re Going on Strike.
JFK's Secret Service agent reflects on presidents' assassination
item.description: On "60 Minutes: A Second Look," a new podcast, former Secret Service agent Clint Hill remembers his emotional interview with Mike Wallace in 1975 about the assassination of President John F. Kennedy.

item.title: Trump, in Georgia, attacks Biden, Harris on Helene response, Biden says he's 'lying'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump spoke at a furniture store in Hurricane Helene-ravaged Valdosta, Georgia, on Monday.

item.title: Jon Stewart Calls Out Trump Supporters’ ‘Bizarro’ Portrayal of Former President: ‘It’s as Though They’ve Created a Fictional Character’
More than 20 feared dead in school bus fire in Thailand
item.description: A bus carrying young students with their teachers caught fire in suburban Bangkok and more than 20 of those on board were feared dead, officials and rescuers said.

item.title: School bus catches fire outside Bangkok and over 20 are feared dead, officials say
item.description: Officials in Thailand say a bus carrying young students and teachers caught fire outside Bangkok and 23 of those on board are feared dead

item.title: South Korea unveils its most powerful missile, which could reach North Korea's underground bunkers
Masdar City: Pioneering Abu Dhabi’s Vision for a Sustainable and Diversified Economy
item.description: Masdar City is driving Abu Dhabi's Falcon Economy and sustainable future. As a free zone and real estate developer, the City is a global hub for innovation, attracting industry leaders in energy, life sciences, agri-tech, space tech, mobility, and AI.

item.title: Pete Rose, MLB's all-time hits leader, dies at 83
item.description: Major League Baseball legend Pete Rose has died at the age of 83, the medical examiner in Clark County, Nevada, confirmed to ABC News on Monday.

item.title: Asheville tragedy shows there are no climate change safe havens: experts
Al Madinah: A Smart, Sustainable City without equal
item.description: The Al Madinah Region Development Authority leads the way for the city’s future with a focus on sustainable, human-centric development, enhancing quality of life while preserving the cultural and historical heritage of the ancient city.
